cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "CrossER: Cross-System Entity Resolution Benchmark"
message: "If you use this benchmark, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - given-names: Nihal
    family-names: Gunukula
    affiliation: Phyvant
  - given-names: Sameer
    family-names: Murthy
    affiliation: Phyvant
repository-code: https://github.com/nihalgunu/CrossER
url: https://github.com/nihalgunu/CrossER
abstract: >-
  CrossER is a hard benchmark for cross-system entity resolution where LLMs fail
  without institutional context. Unlike benchmarks with mixed difficulty, CrossER
  includes only the hardest cases: match pairs have avg 0.29 string similarity
  (look unrelated), no-match pairs have avg 0.94 similarity (look identical).
  The benchmark includes 7,603 pairs (1,141 test) across 5 source systems, with
  86,256 auxiliary context items (migration records, alias tables, code mappings)
  for evaluating context-augmented ER systems.
keywords:
  - entity resolution
  - data matching
  - record linkage
  - enterprise data
  - master data management
  - benchmark
  - dataset
  - LLM evaluation
